transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: How are you doing? I am a little upset here at this point.

Speaker 1: I called after I finally got through to cancel my account.

Speaker 2: I recently had surgery and I have some other medical stuff going on.

Speaker 1: I can no longer take your products.

Speaker 2: I kept texting and emailing to cancel my account and giving instructions to call.

Speaker 1: I would keep trying to call and no one was answering the phone.

Speaker 2: Finally, I got through and someone did answer the phone after I was on hold for 20 minutes.

Speaker 1: He said okay, no problem, we will cancel.

Speaker 2: I said great, I really appreciate that.

Speaker 1: Then they went ahead and they charged my account anyway.

Speaker 2: Then I got a message from someone by the name of Christy.

Speaker 1: I know you guys may not use your correct names.

Speaker 2: Saying that if I get the product, I should send it back.

Speaker 1: I shouldn't send it back to the post office because they may not get it.

Speaker 2: The post office might lose it.

Speaker 1: I have a PO box. I don't know how I am supposed to send it back.

Speaker 2: They don't send it back to the post office.

Speaker 1: Don't worry about that. I'm sorry.

Speaker 2: What was your first and last name?

Speaker 1: I'm sorry. I'm highly medicated right now.

Speaker 2: I just had a knee replacement as well.

Speaker 1: My name is Bob. Last name is Frankenfield.

Speaker 2: Perfect, Mr. Frankenfield.

Speaker 1: We have you there at 2035 Hutchinson Avenue, unit 133R.

Speaker 2: Do you receive mail there?

Speaker 1: Right. 133R is a post office box.

Speaker 2: They do not deliver mail to my home.

Speaker 1: I get you.

Speaker 2: Basically, what the email is telling you to do is to write refuse return to sender

Speaker 1: and let the postal service know, hey, I'm refusing this order.

Speaker 2: I don't want it. Send it back.

Speaker 1: At that point, we definitely would credit the account the full amount.

Speaker 2: The reason you were charged on the 21st, it just posted on the 22nd,

Speaker 1: but it went out that day after you called the agent.

Speaker 2: He did cancel the account out for you, but he wasn't able to stop it

Speaker 1: before it went out, it looks like.

Speaker 2: I do apologize about that.

Speaker 1: You should be able to refuse that order

Speaker 2: and definitely we'll give you a full refund on it

Speaker 1: and you won't get anything else.

Speaker 2: Okay. The problem, though, if I may,

Speaker 1: is that I was trying to reach out to you guys in advance of this

Speaker 2: and I could never freaking get through.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I get you.

Speaker 2: We've been crazy slammed since the holidays.

Speaker 1: We sent a bunch of new advertisements out about our new bills

Speaker 2: and then the email team, they don't let us do the cancellations over the phone.

Speaker 1: That's a different department.

Speaker 2: That's our way, unfortunately, is to have this whole thing unraveled.

Speaker 1: Okay, so even though Christy said,

Speaker 2: don't take it to the post office, I have to take it to the post office

Speaker 1: to return to you guys, correct?

Speaker 2: Yeah, if it's from your P.O. box, just tell them,

Speaker 1: hey, I got this in my P.O. box, but I never wanted this.

Speaker 2: I want to refuse this order and send it back

Speaker 1: and they'll know what to do and it'll come back to us

Speaker 2: and we'll definitely give you the full refund on it.

Speaker 1: Okay, because what scares me, though,

Speaker 2: and I operate a non-profit homeless agency,

Speaker 1: so I know what the postal service is like

Speaker 2: and we deal with them a lot of times

Speaker 1: and they're a mess right now, too.

Speaker 2: When she said that they may not get it back,

Speaker 1: I'm thinking, oh, man, you guys must have history

Speaker 2: with the postal system, the U.S. postal system,

Speaker 1: that they're not reliable and I don't want to send it back

Speaker 2: and then you guys tell me, hey, we never got it, dude,

Speaker 1: so I still get charged, you know?

Speaker 2: Yeah, no worries. Go ahead and refuse that

Speaker 1: and if you can, have them just document that.

Speaker 2: It'll have like a return to sender processed

Speaker 1: on your tracking link to say, hey, you know,

Speaker 2: when you refuse it, could you just, you know,

Speaker 1: have that correspond to the tracking link

Speaker 2: and then we'll see that, even if it doesn't make it back,

Speaker 1: as long as we see that the return to sender is processed.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that makes sense then, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: All right, well, thank you.

Speaker 2: But yeah, just go ahead and get that done for us

Speaker 1: and we will take care of you.

Speaker 2: You'll see that in the next few days

Speaker 1: and then just refuse it, come right back,

Speaker 2: we'll get you that credit, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, and I do appreciate you taking my call.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 2: Enjoy the rest of your day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Take care.

Speaker 1: Bye.
